briefdescription.para: The type of the sub symbol.
Shall be reimplemented by subclasses to create a deep copy of the instance.
Gets the expression to generate this geometry.

detaileddescription.para: This is a hybrid layer, it constructs its own geometry so it does not care about the geometry of its parents.

briefdescription.para: Returns a string that represents this layer type.

detaileddescription.para: Used for serialization. Should match with the string used to register this symbol layer in the registry.

briefdescription.para: Should be reimplemented by subclasses to return a string map that contains the configuration information for the symbol layer.

detaileddescription.para: This is used to serialize a symbol layer perstistently.

briefdescription.para: Will render this symbol layer using the context.

detaileddescription.para: In comparison to other symbols there is no geometry passed in, since the geometry will be created based on information from the context which contains a QgsRenderContext which in turn contains an expression context which is available to the evaluated expression.

parameterdescription.para: The rendering context which will be used to render and to construct a geometry.

briefdescription.para: Set the expression to generate this geometry.
Sets layer's subsymbol. takes ownership of the passed symbol.
Set the type of symbol which should be created.

detaileddescription.para: Should match with the return type of the expression.

parameterdescription.para: The symbol type which shall be used below this symbol.

briefdescription.para: Returns the symbol's sub symbol, if present.

detaileddescription.para: This defines the type of geometry that is created by this generator.

briefdescription.para: Returns the set of attributes referenced by the layer.

detaileddescription.para: This includes attributes required by any data defined properties associated with the layer.
